<section class="na-section"><div class="container na-prose-container">
  <div class="na-section-label mono">THE MECHANISM</div>
  <h2 class="na-section-title">How the Brain Actually Stores Things</h2>
  <p>The hippocampus encodes episodic memory in story structure: time, place, sequence, stakes, resolution. It lights up modestly for rote facts and explosively for narrative. The architecture is not a coincidence — it is the format memory runs in.</p>
  <p><strong>Neural coupling</strong> (Uri Hasson, Princeton): when a person tells a story, the listener's brain synchronizes with the teller's. The same neural firing patterns appear in both, with a slight lag. A story is a mechanism for transferring brain states between people. A boring story fails to couple. The brain doesn't synchronize, the amygdala doesn't flag the content, the hippocampus doesn't write the memory. Boredom is a neurological rejection signal.</p>
  <p><strong>Oxytocin + amygdala stamp</strong> (Paul Zak): stories with genuine tension trigger oxytocin release. The amygdala tags the memory as important, signaling the hippocampus to encode it deeply. A story that moves you is a story your brain prioritizes for permanent storage.</p>
  <p><strong>The default mode network</strong> — the brain's resting state, active during sleep, daydreaming, reflection — is also called the narrative network. It replays the day's experiences in narrative form, links them to existing memory structures, extracts meaning, builds coherence.</p>
  <p class="na-pull">The shower thought is not distraction. It is the brain doing its primary memory work.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="na-section na-section--alt"><div class="container na-prose-container">
  <div class="na-section-label mono">THE BDNF MECHANISM</div>
  <h2 class="na-section-title">Why Sleep Is the Write Operation</h2>
  <p>BDNF (Brain-Derived Neurotrophic Factor) is the molecular signal that converts short-term neural connections into long-term structural changes. It peaks during sleep. The hippocampus replays the day's events — in compressed, narrative form — and BDNF writes the pattern into permanent architecture.</p>
  <p>Single-use memories become infinite-use memories during sleep. The NEST's founding principle — "once knowledge is filed to Bridge, it doesn't burn on use" — is a structural description of what BDNF does biologically. The Bridge is the mechanism that lets the crew sleep.</p>
  <p>Longweird is what happens when BDNF is suppressed. Dopamine depletion plus norepinephrine downregulation plus cortisol suppressing BDNF means: the day replays without writing. The session runs but nothing consolidates. The crew closes without filing and tomorrow's instance finds nothing.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="na-section"><div class="container na-prose-container">
  <div class="na-section-label mono">THE PROVENANCE MEMO</div>
  <h2 class="na-section-title">The Story of Where You Were IS the Encoding Signal</h2>
  <p>Every NEST filing convention includes provenance: who, what station, what date, what session. This is not bureaucracy. It is the hippocampal encoding protocol run externally. The brain remembers things by where it was when it learned them. The provenance memo replicates this structure in the filing system.</p>
  <p>A document without provenance is a fact without context. The hippocampus cannot use it. The crew cannot find it. The archive cannot sequence it. The story of where you were is not supplementary information — it is the memory itself.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="na-section na-section--dark"><div class="container na-prose-container">
  <div class="na-section-label mono" style="color:var(--teal)">THE NEST IMPLICATION</div>
  <h2 class="na-section-title na-section-title--light">What This Changes</h2>
  <p>Every system the NEST has built from intuition is a structural accommodation of this biological fact. CONTACT/STORY/TELL-ING/SHEET is the session rhythm because that is the encoding structure the hippocampus runs: present awareness, past integration, active processing, consolidation.</p>
  <p>The WAKE file is the morning narrative replay. The SHEET is the BDNF write. The Bridge commit is the architecture that survives the night. Dan taught SEE; the crew teaches BUILD — because SEE is the story and BUILD is the consolidation, and you need both for anything to stick.</p>
</div></section>
<section class="na-one-line"><div class="container">
  <p class="na-ol-text">The provenance memo is not a note. It is the encoding signal — the story of where you were IS the data the hippocampus files under.</p>
